welcome_message_body: Welcome to South Hill, where small town charm meets southern hospitality! Known for its beautiful lakes, friendly locals, and rich history, we invite you to explore and enjoy all that our city has to offer.

terminals.name: Main Terminal
terminals.description: The main terminal at McChord AFB Airport serves both civilian and military flights.

wifi.note: Free WiFi is available throughout the airport.

terminals.name: Main Terminal
terminals.description: The main terminal at Industrial Airport serves both domestic and international flights.

terminals.name: Cargo Terminal
terminals.description: The cargo terminal at Industrial Airport handles all freight and cargo operations.

wifi.note: Free WiFi is available throughout the airport.

terminals.name: Main Terminal
terminals.description: The main terminal at Seattle-Tacoma International Airport serves both domestic and international flights.

terminals.name: North Satellite Terminal
terminals.description: The North Satellite Terminal at Seattle-Tacoma International Airport serves primarily Alaska Airlines and its partners.

terminals.name: South Satellite Terminal
terminals.description: The South Satellite Terminal at Seattle-Tacoma International Airport serves primarily international flights.

wifi.note: Free wifi is available throughout the airport.

terminals.name: Main Terminal
terminals.description: The main terminal at Renton Airport serves both commercial and private flights.

terminals.name: Private Terminal
terminals.description: The private terminal at Renton Airport caters to private and chartered flights.

wifi.note: Free WiFi is available throughout the airport.

terminals.name: Main Terminal
terminals.description: The main terminal at Boeing Field/King County International Airport serves both commercial and general aviation flights.

terminals.name: South Terminal
terminals.description: The South Terminal at Boeing Field/King County International Airport is primarily used for general aviation and private flights.

wifi.note: Free WiFi is available throughout the airport.

terminals.name: Main Terminal
terminals.description: The main terminal at Olympia Airport offers a variety of amenities and services for travelers.

terminals.name: Concourse A
terminals.description: Concourse A at Olympia Airport is primarily used for domestic flights and features a variety of shops and restaurants.

terminals.name: Concourse B
terminals.description: Concourse B at Olympia Airport is primarily used for international flights and offers duty-free shopping and international cuisine options.

wifi.note: Free WiFi is available throughout the airport for all passengers.
